Subject: FEATURE: add support for non-disabling semantics in LPN to SBML translator
Date: Tue, 30 Nov 2010 10:42:04 -0700
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.936)

Need to add support for non-disabling transitions in LPN to SBML  
translator.

This entails adding a new event which samples the enabling condition  
and sets a Boolean for the transition to true to record this.

For example:

p0 - {e0}[d0]<a0> -> t0
p0 - {e1}[d1]<a1> -> t1

trigger (e0 & p0)
persistent true
delay 0
assign
	t0:=T

trigger (t0)
persistent false
delay d0
assign
	p0:=F
	t0:=F
	t1:=F  <-- if t1 is also non-disabling
	<a0>


